# Movie Concept — Build Spec

A new SwiftUI concept for this repo. Follow the existing `AGENTS.md` conventions
(concept folders, styling in component files, no over-engineering, short inline
comments only on tweakable values).

## Goal

One screen: a full-screen 360° panorama of a movie theater. Tap a seat button to
jump to that seat's viewpoint (the panorama image swaps). A "Book" button shows a
confirmation overlay. That's the whole concept.

Touch-drag to look around first. Gyroscope is a later add, not v1.

## Folder structure to create

```text
wallet/wallet/Movie/
  Assets/                 3 panorama imagesets: pano_entrance, pano_front, pano_back
  Components/
    PanoramaView.swift    SceneKit sphere + panorama texture (the only hard part)
  Models/
    Viewpoint.swift       image name + stats per seat
  Pages/
    MovieMainPage.swift   the full screen: panorama + seat buttons + book overlay
```

No Config or Helpers folders for v1 — keep it minimal. Inline any constants where
they're tweaked.

## Assets

Three equirectangular (2:1) panorama PNGs go into `Movie/Assets` as imagesets named:
- `pano_entrance` — standing at the back / aisle
- `pano_front` — front-center seat (screen looms large)
- `pano_back` — back-corner seat (screen small, angled)

(I'll drag the PNGs into the asset catalog myself in Xcode.)

## App start

To show this concept first, set the entry view in
`wallet/wallet/iosconceptsApp.swift`:

```swift
WindowGroup {
    MovieMainPage()
}
```

## Build order

1. `PanoramaView` — SceneKit sphere, inward normals, panorama texture, touch-drag
   look-around. Get one image rendering and draggable. This is the only risky piece.
2. `Viewpoint` model + the three viewpoints.
3. `MovieMainPage` — show the panorama, two/three seat buttons that swap the image,
   a stats strip, and a Book button that toggles a confirmation overlay.
4. Polish later: gyroscope (CMMotionManager), cross-fade on swap, haptics.

